  44. /* Requests from the debugger to the runtime system */

  46. ‌enum debugger_request {
  47.   REQ_SET_EVENT = 'e',          /* uint32_t pos */
  48.   /* Set an event on the instruction at position pos */
  49.   REQ_SET_BREAKPOINT = 'B',     /* uint32_t pos, (char k) */
  50.   /* Set a breakpoint at position pos */
  51.   /* In profiling mode, the breakpoint kind is set to k */
  52.   REQ_RESET_INSTR = 'i',        /* uint32_t pos */
  53.   /* Clear an event or breapoint at position pos, restores initial instr. */
  54.   REQ_CHECKPOINT = 'c',         /* no args */
  55.   /* Checkpoint the runtime system by forking a child process.
  56.      Reply is pid of child process or -1 if checkpoint failed. */
  57.   REQ_GO = 'g',                 /* uint32_t n */
  58.   /* Run the program for n events.
  59.      Reply is one of debugger_reply described below. */
  60.   REQ_STOP = 's',               /* no args */
  61.   /* Terminate the runtime system */
  62.   REQ_WAIT = 'w',               /* no args */
  63.   /* Reap one dead child (a discarded checkpoint). */
  64.   REQ_INITIAL_FRAME = '0',      /* no args */
  65.   /* Set current frame to bottom frame (the one currently executing).
  66.      Reply is stack offset and current pc. */
  67.   REQ_GET_FRAME = 'f',          /* no args */
  68.   /* Return current frame location (stack offset + current pc). */
  69.   REQ_SET_FRAME = 'S',          /* uint32_t stack_offset */
  70.   /* Set current frame to given stack offset. No reply. */
  71.   REQ_UP_FRAME = 'U',           /* uint32_t n */
  72.   /* Move one frame up. Argument n is size of current frame (in words).
  73.      Reply is stack offset and current pc, or -1 if top of stack reached. */
  74.   REQ_SET_TRAP_BARRIER = 'b',   /* uint32_t offset */
  75.   /* Set the trap barrier at the given offset. */
  76.   REQ_GET_LOCAL = 'L',          /* uint32_t slot_number */
  77.   /* Return the local variable at the given slot in the current frame.
  78.      Reply is one value. */
  79.   REQ_GET_ENVIRONMENT = 'E',    /* uint32_t slot_number */
  80.   /* Return the local variable at the given slot in the heap environment
  81.      of the current frame. Reply is one value. */
  82.   REQ_GET_GLOBAL = 'G',         /* uint32_t global_number */
  83.   /* Return the specified global variable. Reply is one value. */
  84.   REQ_GET_ACCU = 'A',           /* no args */
  85.   /* Return the current contents of the accumulator. Reply is one value. */
  86.   REQ_GET_HEADER = 'H',         /* mlvalue v */
  87.   /* As REQ_GET_OBJ, but sends only the header. */
  88.   REQ_GET_FIELD = 'F',          /* mlvalue v, uint32_t fieldnum */
  89.   /* As REQ_GET_OBJ, but sends only one field. */
  90.   REQ_MARSHAL_OBJ = 'M',        /* mlvalue v */
  91.   /* Send a copy of the data structure rooted at v, using the same
  92.      format as [caml_output_value]. */
  93.   REQ_GET_CLOSURE_CODE = 'C',   /* mlvalue v */
  94.   /* Send the code address of the given closure.
  95.      Reply is one uint32_t. */
  96.   REQ_SET_FORK_MODE = 'K'       /* uint32_t m */
  97.   /* Set whether to follow the child (m=0) or the parent on fork. */
  98. };

  100. /* Replies to a REQ_GO request. All replies are followed by three uint32_t:
  101.    - the value of the event counter
  102.    - the position of the stack
  103.    - the current pc.
  104.    The REP_CODE_DEBUG_INFO reply is also followed by:
  105.    - the newly added debug information.
  106.    The REP_CODE_{UN,}LOADED reply is also followed by:
  107.    - the code fragment index. */

  109. ‌enum debugger_reply {
  110.   REP_EVENT = 'e',
  111.   /* Event counter reached 0. */
  112.   REP_BREAKPOINT = 'b',
  113.   /* Breakpoint hit. */
  114.   REP_EXITED = 'x',
  115.   /* Program exited by calling exit or reaching the end of the source. */
  116.   REP_TRAP = 's',
  117.   /* Trap barrier crossed. */
  118.   REP_UNCAUGHT_EXC = 'u',
  119.   /* Program exited due to a stray exception. */
  120.   REP_CODE_DEBUG_INFO = 'D',
  121.   /* Additional debug info loaded. */
  122.   REP_CODE_LOADED = 'L',
  123.   /* Additional code loaded. */
  124.   REP_CODE_UNLOADED = 'U',
  125.   /* Additional code unloaded. */
  126. };
